headline: General Mills Guidance Reset And Leadership Change Put Execution In Focus
summary: General Mills (NYSE:GIS) cut its full year fiscal 2026 sales and earnings guidance, pointing to weaker consumer sentiment and more volatile category demand. The company framed the guidance reset as a response to recent trading conditions and a reassessment of near term expectations. Former Chief Information Officer Donald Monk left General Mills to join Hormel Foods, marking a change in senior leadership during this period. General Mills operates a broad portfolio of packaged food brands,...
